                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13820954" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 05:26:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Christian, it seems that your latest change breaks unit test on the main module:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Failed tests:   testGetLogManager(org.apache.karaf.main.util.BootstrapLogManagerTest): File should exist at target/log/karaf.log&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Did you try to execute the utests on main ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I&apos;m taking a look on that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13820964" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 05:44:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was just a &quot;timing&quot; issue: randomly (depending of the load of the machine), the assertion occurred before the handler created the log file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just introduced a small delay to give the time to the handler to create the log file and check the assertion after.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13820968" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 05:49:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, the delay doesn&apos;t seem to be enough. The test still randomly fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m digging.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821000" author="chris@die-schneider.net" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 06:42:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will also look into it. No idea how it is related to my change but probably it is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821013" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 06:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s just because you added this unit test &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821067" author="chris@die-schneider.net" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 08:45:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well .. in fact this is true .. the unit test introduced a side effect as I set a System property. This then influenced the other test depending on unit test order.&lt;br/&gt;
I refactored the code so it can be tested without changing system properties.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821546" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 17:17:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested and it&apos;s now fixed. Thanks Christian.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
